 :FidoNet: /n./ A worldwide hobbyist network of personal computers which
exchanges mail, discussion groups, and files. Founded in 1984 and originally
consisting only of IBM PCs and compatibles, FidoNet now includes such diverse
machines as Apple ][s, Ataris, Amigas, and Unix systems. FidoNet has grown
rapidly and in early 1996 has approximately 38000 nodes.